# Up Final Architecture Rule

## Mission
- Build and ship only in `up-final`.
- Keep `reference-app` and `reference-app-fitness` strictly read-only.
- Prioritize maintainability, testability, and migration safety over quick patches.

## Workspace Boundary (Hard)
- **Primary Workspace**: All implementation must happen in `up-final`.
- **Reference Only**: You may read from `@reference-app` and `@reference-app-fitness`.
- **No Modification**: Never create, edit, move, or delete files in reference folders.

## Layering Contract
- `src/logic/core/`: Pure domain logic only (framework-agnostic, deterministic).
- `src/services/`: External integrations (Firebase/Auth/API/storage).
- `src/stores/`: Global state orchestration.
- `src/hooks/`: UI-facing adapters that connect store/service/logic.
- `src/components/`: Presentational and composable UI units.

## Non-Negotiables
- No business logic inside UI components.
- No direct external SDK calls from components (go through service layer).
- Prefer refactor over patch when structure blocks scalability.
- If a file becomes too large/complex, split by responsibility before adding more features.
